quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  92,15,"None except the most wicked will enter it."
  92,16,"The one who denied and turned away."
  92,17,"He will be far away from the most pious. (The first Caliph S. Abu Bakr Siddiq)"
  92,18,"Who gives his wealth in order to be pure."
  92,19,"And no one has done a favour to him, for which he should be compensated."
  92,20,"He desires only to please his Lord, the Supreme."
  92,21,"And indeed, soon he will be very pleased."
  93,1,"By oath of the late morning,"
  93,2,"And by oath of the night when it covers,"
  93,3,"Your Lord has not forsaken you nor does He dislike you!"
  93,4,"And indeed the latter is better for you than the former."
  93,5,"And indeed your Lord will soon give you so much that you will be pleased. (Allah seeks to please the Holy Prophet – peace and blessings be upon him.)"
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan, so provided you shelter?"
  93,7,"And found you deeply engrossed in His love, so directed you?"
  93,8,"And found you in need, so made you prosperous?"
  93,9,"Therefore do not oppress the orphan."
  93,10,"And do not rebuke the beggar."
  93,11,"And abundantly proclaim the favours of your Lord."
  94,1,"Did We not widen your bosom?"
  94,2,"And relieve you of the burden –"
  94,3,"Which had broken your back?"
  94,4,"And We have exalted your remembrance for you."
  94,5,"So indeed with hardship is ease."
  94,6,"Indeed with hardship is ease."
  94,7,"So when you finish the prayer, strive in supplication."
  94,8,"And incline towards your Lord."
